---
title: Chicken Tikka Masala over Basmati Rice
description: Ready to make restaurant-worthy chicken tikka masala in your own kitchen in just 25 minutes? It’s as easy as: 1. Brown your chicken with onion and garlic. 2. Simmer in your creamy sauce laced with aromatic garam masala, warming ginger, and umami-packed tomato paste. 3. Spoon it all over buttery basmati rice with fresh cilantro and thin slices of chili pepper if you like a little heat. Oh, and how could we forget 4: dig the heck in!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chicken-tikka-masala-55d3bdc7.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-tikka-masala-5fc6c7d989573e34d618a43c-752a6af3.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Indian
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 550 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-tikka-masala-5fc6c7d989573e34d618a43c
time required: 25 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry all produce.  

In a #small pot{}, combine @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.  

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.  

Meanwhile, halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1}; thinly slice one half (slice whole onion for 4). Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Thinly slice @Chili Pepper{1}.

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Toss in a #medium bowl{} with @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.  

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium high heat. Add sliced onion and a pinch of @salt{}; cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.  

Add chicken and cook until browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Stir ginger and @Garam Masala{2%teaspoon} into pan. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.  

Stir in @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce}; cook for ~{1%minute}.  

Pour in 1/2 cup water (1 cup for 4 servings), @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and @Sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4), stirring until smooth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low; simmer until sauce is thickened and chicken is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. (If sauce is too thick, add a splash or two more water.)  

Stir in half the cilantro. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.  

> TIP: If you like your chicken tikka masala a bit sweeter, add a pinch more sugar.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.  

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} or #plates{}. Top with chicken tikka masala. Garnish with remaining cilantro and a pinch of chili if desired.